MESHLOADER LOGIC:

For each mesh in the asset:
    For each primitive in that mesh:
        1. Find the POSITION accessor → read all vertex positions
        2. Find the NORMAL accessor → read all normals (if they exist)
        3. Find the TEXCOORD_0 accessor → read all UVs (if they exist)
        4. Find the indices accessor → read all indices
        5. Interleave positions + normals + UVs into one vector<float>
        6. Build the VertexAttribute layout describing what's in there
        7. Call mesh.setup() with that data
        8. Push the mesh into the model